{"word":"ἐπάναγκες","slug":"ἐπάναγκες","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b><el>ἐπάναγϰες</el></b> [<el><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:ἐπί\">ἐπί</a>, <a class=\"S\" href=\"S:ἀνάγκη\">ἀνάγκη</a></el>; this form, the <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ nt.\">nt.</a> of <el>ἐπανάγϰης</el>, which is used only in the <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ nt.\">nt.</a>, signifies ‘compulsory’] in <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ NT\">NT</a> only as <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ adv.\">adv.</a> <b>necessarily:</b> <el>τὰ ἐ.</el> the things that are necessary, i.e. to do in accordance with established custom <b><a href='B:510 15:28'>Ac 15:28</a>.</b> <center id=\"nav_bottom\"> <a id=\"left_arrow\" href=\"S:ἐπαναγαγεῖν\">&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;</a> <a id=\"bottom_home\" href=\"S:#1.Table of Contents\">&emsp;&emsp;</a> <a id=\"right_arrow\" href=\"S:ἐπανάγω\">&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;</a> </center> "}]}